===Intransitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|seal||}}
# To [[hunt]] for seals (marine animals)
#: ''They're organizing a protest against '''sealing'''.''

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|seal||}}
# To prevent from being [[opened]] without visible [[damage]].
#: ''The cover is '''sealed'''.  If anyone tries to open it, we'll know about it.''
# To prevent people or vehicles from [[crossing]].
#: ''The border has been '''sealed''' until the fugitives are found.''
# To close securely to prevent [[leakage]].
#: ''I've '''sealed''' the bottle to keep the contents fresh.''
# To place in a sealed container.
#: ''I've '''sealed''' the documents in this envelope.''
# (''chess'') To place a notation of ones next move in a sealed envelope to be opened after an [[adjournment]].
#: ''After thinking for half an hour, the champion '''sealed''' his move.''

